[Event "Baker Bridge - Fourth Suit Forcing, NMF, Help Suit Game Try"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:K64.KQ974.4.AJ65 JT8.JT2.KJ73.K73 AQ972.85.A96.QT4 53.A63.QT852.982"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1H pass 1S pass 2C pass 2D pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH might well bid 3NT at his second turn, and this may turn out to be the 
final contract anyway.

But it doesn't hurt to bid 2\D (Fourth Suit Forcing) just to 
see if SOUTH happens to have three \Ss. She does, so 4\S becomes the better game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:85.QJ97.AQ9.A843 JT4.A3.T862.KT76 AK763.KT84.K4.52 Q92.652.J753.QJ9"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1C pass 1S pass 1NT pass 2D pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST isn't strong enough to make a Reverse bid of 2\H at his second turn.

WEST uses the 2\D (NMF) bid to ask EAST for further description. 
EAST should first show a 4-card \H suit, and next show 3-card \S support.

Change EAST's \H9 to the \S9 and the contract would be 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "N:K942.8.87542.Q97 53.QJT32.AQ6.T63 AQJT7.765.3.AK84 86.AK94.KJT9.J52"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
pass pass 1S pass 2S pass 3H pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH's 3\H bid is a Help Suit Game Try.

NORTH barely had enough strength to respond in the first place, but revaluing the hand, 
(and particularly the singleton \H), makes it worth a 
raise to game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
